article.headline: Rice 56, San Jose State 50
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Michael Harris had 15 points and 18 rebounds to lead Rice past San Jose State 56-50 on Friday night. J.R. Harrison scored 11 points and Brock Gillespie added 10 for Rice (15-10, 9-6 Western Athletic Conference), which remains third in the WAC standings. Harris now needs 27 points to become Rice's all-time scoring leader. Marquin Chandler had 12 points and 10 rebounds for San Jose State (6-19, 3-12), which has lost seven straight and fell to 1-12 on the road. Eric Bloom added 14 points for San Jose State.
